fields.title: Classic Spaghetti Carbonara
fields.description: A traditional Italian pasta dish with eggs, cheese, pancetta, and black pepper.
fields.ingredients:
400g spaghetti
200g pancetta or guanciale
4 large eggs
100g Pecorino Romano
100g Parmigiano-Reggiano
Black pepper
Salt
fields.instructions:
1. Bring a large pot of salted water to boil
2. Cook spaghetti according to package instructions
3. While pasta cooks, whisk eggs and cheese
4. Cook pancetta until crispy
5. Combine hot pasta with egg mixture
6. Add pancetta and plenty of black pepper

fields.content: Tried this recipe last night - it was perfect! The key really is using good quality cheese.
